#### Problem 004: Non-empty contractAddress on an Errored Transaction or Trace

	Transaction receipt holds a non-empty contractAddress field, but the contract did not get created.
	
#### Description

[This transaction](https://etherscan.io/tx/0x1a03e6f3a89a65a2cd146a215cbb8427f29c8695517dddc6a0901c9fbe179eb0) generated an error, but it's `contractAddress` field is non-empty. A naive interpretation of the `contractAddress` field may lead one to think a contract was created, when in reality it wasn't. Etherscan reports that there was a contract creation, but also reports an error. The byte code for the 'contract' address is empty.

```
231670.1	1442209038	0x5d4f265cf6f01640dab2fed8ccedf7a663d09151071afc2d439234df0aaa6eec
              -  receipt.contractAddress: 0x3dbdeeafa2aca6c8c4f6e442b07bb575fc5658a9
              -	48777.0	create	Outofgas
              -	231670.1	call	Outofgas
             0-	231670.1	create	Outofgas
```

#### Suggestion

Identify this oddity by finding traces of `type` create on a transaction (or trace) that has non-empty `error` field. This is similar to oddity 002.

#### QuickBlocks Command

	getTrans -t -v 0x1a03e6f3a89a65a2cd146a215cbb8427f29c8695517dddc6a0901c9fbe179eb0
